President Donald J. Trump has declared the continuation of the national emergency that was initially declared on September 14, 2001, in response to the terrorist attacks of September 11, 2001. This declaration is in accordance with section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act. The president states that due to the ongoing terrorist threat, the national emergency and the powers and authorities granted to deal with it must remain in effect beyond September 14, 2018. The notice will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.